CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 3, 1945, pg. 3 reads: "First Anniversary Celebration - the Pittsburgh Interracial Action Council celebrated its first anniversary, at ....Henry, with an elaborate banquet, Monday evening. Over 200 guests attended the celebration... The center photo shows the guests enjoying the sumptuous meal which preceded the program and social hour...Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Women and men seated at banquet tables, including Connie Scott wearing dark dress with light colored stitching seated on stage at head table, in interior with floral curtain and egg and dart moldings, for the Pittsburgh Interracial Action Council anniversary celebration
